    <h2 id="info-collect"><span class="num">1.</span>What information we collect</h2>
 
    <h3>Personal information you disclose to us</h3>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We collect personal information that you provide to us.</p>
    <p>We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you express an interest in our Services, participate in activities, or contact us. This may include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Names</li>
      <li>Email addresses</li>
      <li>Debit/credit card numbers (handled by Stripe — we never see your full card number)</li>
      <li>Photos uploaded for outfit analysis</li>
    </ul>
 
    <h3>Payment data</h3>
    <p>If you choose to make purchases, we collect data necessary to process your payment, such as your payment instrument number and security code. <strong>All payment data is handled and stored by Stripe.</strong> You can review their privacy notice at <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">stripe.com/privacy</a>.</p>
 
    <h3>Information collected from other sources</h3>
    <p>To improve our Services and marketing, we may obtain information about you from public databases, advertising platforms (like TikTok Ads), and similar sources. This typically includes IP addresses and behavior data for advertising purposes.</p>
 
    <h2 id="info-use"><span class="num">2.</span>How we process your information</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We process your information to provide, improve, and administer our Services, communicate with you, for security and fraud prevention, and to comply with law.</p>
    <p>We process your personal information for the following reasons:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>To deliver and facilitate the Services to you</li>
      <li>To respond to user inquiries and offer support</li>
      <li>To send you marketing and promotional communications (you can opt out anytime)</li>
      <li>To deliver targeted advertising to you</li>
      <li>To process AI-based outfit analysis on the photos you upload</li>
      <li>To save or protect an individual's vital interest, such as to prevent harm</li>
    </ul>
 
    <h2 id="legal-bases"><span class="num">3.</span>Legal bases for processing</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We only process your personal information when we believe it is necessary and we have a valid legal reason to do so under applicable law.</p>
    <p>The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and UK GDPR require us to explain the valid legal bases we rely on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent.</strong> We process your information if you have given us permission. You can withdraw consent at any time.</li>
      <li><strong>Performance of a contract.</strong> We may process your information when necessary to fulfill our contractual obligations to you.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests.</strong> We may process your information when reasonably necessary to achieve our legitimate business interests.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligations.</strong> We may process your information where required for compliance with our legal obligations.</li>
      <li><strong>Vital interests.</strong> We may process your information to protect your vital interests or those of others.</li>
    </ul>
 
    <h2 id="share"><span class="num">4.</span>When and with whom we share information</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We share information only with specific third parties who help us operate Pickr.</p>
    <p>The third parties we may share personal information with include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Advertising and lead generation:</strong> TikTok Ads</li>
      <li><strong>AI service providers:</strong> OpenRouter (for outfit analysis)</li>
      <li><strong>Payment processing:</strong> Stripe</li>
      <li><strong>Email services:</strong> Formspree</li>
      <li><strong>Website hosting:</strong> Vercel</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We may also share your personal information in connection with business transfers (such as a merger or acquisition).</p>
 
    <h2 id="ai"><span class="num">5.</span>Our AI-based products</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We offer AI-powered outfit analysis and feedback.</p>
    <p>As part of our Services, we offer products powered by artificial intelligence and machine learning ("AI Products"). Specifically, we use AI for image analysis to provide outfit feedback.</p>
    <p>All personal information processed using our AI Products is handled in line with this Privacy Notice and our agreements with third parties (specifically OpenRouter). Photos you upload are sent to our AI service provider for analysis and are not stored after the analysis is complete.</p>
 
    <h2 id="retain"><span class="num">6.</span>How long we keep information</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We keep your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Notice unless otherwise required by law.</p>
    <p>When we have no ongoing legitimate business need to process your personal information, we will either delete or anonymize it, or securely store it and isolate it from any further processing until deletion is possible.</p>
 
    <h2 id="minors"><span class="num">7.</span>Information from minors</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> We do not knowingly collect data from or market to children under 18 years of age.</p>
    <p>By using the Services, you represent that you are at least 18 or that you are the parent or guardian of such a minor and consent to such minor dependent's use of the Services. If we learn that personal information from users under 18 has been collected, we will deactivate the account and take reasonable measures to promptly delete such data.</p>
    <p>If you become aware of any data we may have collected from a child under 18, please contact us at <a href="mailto:trypickr@gmail.com">trypickr@gmail.com</a>.</p>
 
    <h2 id="rights"><span class="num">8.</span>Your privacy rights</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> In some regions (like the EEA, UK, and Switzerland), you have rights that allow greater access to and control over your personal information.</p>
    <p>You have certain rights under applicable data protection laws. These may include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Right to access and obtain a copy of your personal information</li>
      <li>Right to request rectification or erasure</li>
      <li>Right to restrict the processing of your personal information</li>
      <li>Right to data portability (if applicable)</li>
      <li>Right not to be subject to automated decision-making</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, please email <a href="mailto:trypickr@gmail.com">trypickr@gmail.com</a>. We will consider and act upon any request in accordance with applicable data protection laws.</p>
 
    <h3>Withdrawing consent</h3>
    <p>If we are relying on your consent to process your personal information, you have the right to withdraw it at any time by contacting us. This will not affect the lawfulness of processing before its withdrawal.</p>
 
    <h3>Opting out of marketing</h3>
    <p>You can unsubscribe from our marketing communications at any time by contacting us at <a href="mailto:trypickr@gmail.com">trypickr@gmail.com</a>. We may still send you service-related messages necessary for your account.</p>
 
    <h2 id="updates"><span class="num">9.</span>Updates to this notice</h2>
    <p><strong><em>In short:</em></strong> Yes, we will update this notice as necessary to stay compliant with relevant laws.</p>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Notice from time to time. The updated version will be indicated by an updated "Last updated" date at the top of this Privacy Notice. We encourage you to review this Privacy Notice frequently to stay informed.</p>
 
    <h2 id="contact"><span class="num">10.</span>How to contact us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or comments about this notice, you may email us at <a href="mailto:trypickr@gmail.com">trypickr@gmail.com</a> or contact us by post at:</p>
    <p style="background: var(--cream-deep); padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px;">
      <strong>Pickr</strong><br/>
      Carrer de Pau VI, 76A<br/>
      Sant Cugat del Vallès, Barcelona 08173<br/>
      Spain
    </p>
 
    <h3>Reviewing or deleting your data</h3>
    <p>You have the right to request access to the personal information we collect from you, details about how we have processed it, correct inaccuracies, or delete your personal information. To make a request, email <a href="mailto:trypickr@gmail.com">trypickr@gmail.com</a>.</p>
 
